Text forecast

Today

Tonight

Scotland and northern England will see rain gradually clear to the east, followed by clear spells overnight for England and Wales and locally dense fog patches throughout most of the UK.

Tomorrow

Tuesday

Tomorrow, fog may linger in some parts of southern England, but much of the rest of the UK should be dry with spells of sunshine. Cloudier in NW Scotland with drizzle.

Outlook

Outlook for Wednesday to Friday

On Wednesday, rain will move into Northern Ireland and Scotland from the west, with England and Wales drier but still chilly. Once again, some mist and fog patches could linger in places. For Thursday, wet and windy in the north, breezier and less cold in the south. Rain should push south-east across many areas on Friday, followed by showers in the north.
